The machine object is not opaque in C, but most fields are runtime-owned.

| Field | Meaning | External usage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `vars` | Persistent variable storage | Read through `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_vars(...)` |
| `_active_vars` | Internal active variable pointer | Internal |
| `stack` | Internal execution stack | Internal |
| `stack_size` | Current internal stack depth | Internal |
| `ended` | Internal terminal flag | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_is_ended(...)` |
| `entered_root` | Internal root-entry flag | Internal |
| `hooks` | Installed abstract-hook table pointer | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_hooks(...)` |
| `hook_user_data` | Installed abstract-hook user pointer | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_hooks(...)` |
| `event_checks` | Installed event-check table pointer | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks(...)` |
| `event_check_user_data` | Installed event-check user pointer | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks(...)` |
| `event_checks_mounted` | Whether a complete event-check table is mounted | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks(...)` and `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_last_error(...)` |
| `last_error` | Internal last-error buffer | Prefer `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_last_error(...)` |

## Function Reference

| Function | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_create()` | Allocate and initialize a machine on the heap; default hosted profile only, omitted when `PYFCSTM_GENERATED_NO_HEAP` is defined |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_destroy(machine)` | Destroy a heap-allocated machine; default hosted profile only, omitted when `PYFCSTM_GENERATED_NO_HEAP` is defined |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_init(machine)` | Cold-initialize or reset a machine |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_hot_start(machine, state_id, vars)` | Start from a concrete generated state id and variable snapshot |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_hooks(machine, hooks, user_data)` | Register abstract lifecycle hooks |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks(machine, event_checks, user_data)` | Register and validate the event-check table |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_cycle(machine)` | Execute one cycle using the installed event-check table |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_vars(machine)` | Read persistent variables |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_is_ended(machine)` | Test whether the machine has ended |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_current_state_id(machine)` | Read the current leaf-state id |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_current_state_path(machine)` | Read the current leaf-state full path for diagnostics |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_current_state_name(machine)` | Read the current leaf-state short name |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_last_error(machine)` | Read the last error message |
| `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_dsl_source()` | Read the embedded canonical model export |

### Function Usage Notes

- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_create()` /
  `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_destroy()`:
  use these if you want heap allocation managed by the generated runtime. They
  belong to the default hosted profile; in the no-heap profile, allocate the
  machine object yourself and call `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_init()` or
  `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_hot_start(...)`.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_init()`:
  use this for stack-allocated machines or to reset an existing machine. After
  reset, reinstall hooks and event checks as needed.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_hot_start()`:
  `initial_vars` must describe a complete persistent-state snapshot compatible
  with `initial_state_id`. Hot start preserves already-installed hook and
  event-check tables.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks()`:
  for eventful machines, provide a complete generated table. Partial tables are
  rejected and leave the machine non-runnable for `cycle()`.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_cycle()`:
  executes one cycle using the currently installed event-check table. If the
  table is missing or incomplete, the call returns
  `{{ machine_macro_name(model) }}_FAILURE` and `last_error` explains why.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_vars()`:
  returns a read-only pointer; if you need a mutable external snapshot, copy the
  struct value out first.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_last_error()`:
  useful after any API call that returned `{{ machine_macro_name(model) }}_FAILURE`.
- `{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_dsl_source()`:
  useful for diagnostics, traceability, or exposing the canonical / normalized
  model export to tooling.

## Minimal Complete Flow

```c
#include "machine.h"
#include <stdio.h>

{% if abstract_ns.rows -%}
static void generated_hook(
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} *machine,
    const {{ machine_class_name(model) }}ExecutionContext *ctx,
    void *user_data
)
{
    (void)machine;
    (void)user_data;
    printf("hook: action=%d state=%d stage=%d\n", (int)ctx->action_id, (int)ctx->state_id, (int)ctx->action_stage_id);
}

{% endif -%}
{% if event_ns.items -%}
typedef struct DriverState {
    int trigger_selected_event;
} DriverState;

static int selected_event_check(
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} *machine,
    const {{ machine_class_name(model) }}EventContext *ctx,
    void *user_data
)
{
    DriverState *driver = (DriverState *)user_data;
    (void)machine;
    (void)ctx;
    return driver->trigger_selected_event;
}

static int inactive_event_check(
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} *machine,
    const {{ machine_class_name(model) }}EventContext *ctx,
    void *user_data
)
{
    (void)machine;
    (void)ctx;
    (void)user_data;
    return 0;
}

{% endif -%}
int main(void)
{
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }} machine;
{% if abstract_ns.rows %}
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}Hooks hooks = {{ machine_class_name(model) | upper }}_HOOKS_INIT;
{% endif -%}
{% if event_ns.items %}
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}EventChecks event_checks = {{ machine_class_name(model) | upper }}_EVENT_CHECKS_INIT;
    DriverState driver = {0};
{% endif %}

    if (!{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_init(&machine)) {
        return 1;
    }
{% if abstract_ns.rows %}
    hooks.{{ abstract_ns.rows[0]['hook_name'] }} = generated_hook;
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_hooks(&machine, &hooks, NULL);
{% endif %}
{% if event_ns.items %}
    /* Fill every generated event-check field before cycle(). */
{% for event_path in event_ns.items %}
    event_checks.{{ event_check_field_id_name(event_path) }} = {% if loop.first %}selected_event_check{% else %}inactive_event_check{% endif %};
{% endfor %}
    {{ machine_class_name(model) }}_set_event_checks(&machine, &event_checks, &driver);
{% endif %}
    if (!{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_cycle(&machine)) {
        return 2;
    }
{% if event_ns.items %}
    driver.trigger_selected_event = 1;
    if (!{{ machine_class_name(model) }}_cycle(&machine)) {
        return 3;
    }
{% endif %}
    printf("state id: %d\n", (int){{ machine_class_name(model) }}_current_state_id(&machine));
    return 0;
}
```

